<p class=mibilllongbillnumber>HOUSE BILL NO. 4510</p>

<p class=mibilldonotdelete><img width=624 height=250
src="HB4510_files/image001.png"
alt="May 04, 2023, Introduced by Reps. Maddock, Carra, DeBoyer, Alexander, Bierlein, Markkanen, Rigas, Paquette, Johnsen, Prestin, Hoadley, Neyer, BeGole, Meerman, St. Germaine, Smit, Fox, Friske, DeSana and Bollin and referred to the Committee on Government Operations."></p>

<p class=mibilltitle><a name=BillTitle>A bill to amend 1976 PA 451, entitled</a></p>

<p class=mibilltitleline2>&quot;The revised school code,&quot;</p>

<p class=mibilltitleline3>(MCL 380.1 to 380.1852) by adding section 1146a.</p>

<p class=mibillenactment>the people of the state of michigan enact:</p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><a name="sec_import_start_380_1146a"></a><span
class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;background:white'>Sec. 1146a. (1)
Subject to subsection (2), a public school shall ensure that every
multiple-occupancy restroom or changing area designated for pupil use must be
used by individuals based only on biological sex.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(2) This section does not apply to an individual entering a
multiple-occupancy restroom or changing area designated for use by the opposite
biological sex when entering in any of the following circumstances:</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(a) For custodial purposes.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(b) For maintenance or inspection purposes.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(c) To render medical assistance.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(d) To accompany a pupil needing assistance when the
assisting individual is an employee of the public school or the pupil's parent
or legal guardian or authorized caregiver.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(e) To receive assistance in using the multiple-occupancy
restroom or changing area.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(f) When the restroom has been temporarily designated for use
by that individual's biological sex.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(3) As used in this section:</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(a) &quot;Authorized caregiver&quot; means a caregiver as
that term is defined in section 3 of the designated caregiver act, 2016 PA 85,
MCL 333.26283.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(b) &quot;Biological sex&quot; means the physical condition
of being male or female, as stated on an individual's original birth
certificate.</span></span></p>

<p class=mibillnonstatute><span class=mibillnew><span style='color:black;
background:white'>(c) &quot;Multiple-occupancy restroom or changing area&quot;
means an area in a public school building designed or designated to be used by
more than 1 pupil at a time, where pupils may be in various stages of undress
in the presence of other pupils or individuals. The term may include, but is
not limited to, a school restroom, locker room, changing room, or shower room.</span></span></p>

